  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through multiple strategies, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Regulations\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for large cash transactions\n\n2. Investigation Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing money movement across jurisdictions\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Using sophisticated digital tracking technologies\n\n3. Legal Frameworks\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- International cooperation through treaties\n- Prosecution of complex financial crimes\n\n4. Technological Approaches\n- Advanced data analytics\n- Blockchain tracking\n- Machine learning detection algorithms\n- Digital transaction monitoring systems\n\n5. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- International sanctions\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and technological strategies.",
